                        <div class="question-text">A rectangular field has dimensions 127.3 ± 0.5 m by 89.6 ± 0.3 m. Calculate the area with proper uncertainty.</div>
                        <div class="toggle-icon">+</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="answer-content">
                        <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                        <p>Area = length × width = 127.3 × 89.6 = 11,406.08 m²</p>
                        <p><strong>Uncertainty calculation for multiplication:</strong></p>
                        <p>Relative uncertainty in length: δl/l = 0.5/127.3 = 0.00393</p>
                        <p>Relative uncertainty in width: δw/w = 0.3/89.6 = 0.00335</p>
                        <p>Combined relative uncertainty: √(0.00393² + 0.00335²) = 0.00517</p>
                        <p>Absolute uncertainty: δA = A × 0.00517 = 11,406 × 0.00517 = 59 m²</p>
                        <p><strong>Final answer: A = 11,400 ± 60 m²</strong></p>
